The paper focuses on gait recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves deep learning and neural networks, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of gait recognition in crime prevention and forensic identification, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and security and privacy (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves image and video processing, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR).
